FBIS3-58119 "drweu000__a94001" FBIS-WEU-93-000-A Document Type:Daily Report 2 December 1993 ANNEX International Affairs Zhirinovskiy Apologizes For Attacks on Germany LD0601142194 Hamburg DPA in German 1345 GMT 6 Jan 94--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY LD0601142194 Hamburg DPA Language: German Article Type:BFN [Excerpt] Vienna/Moscow (DPA) -- In an interview with the Austrian magazine NEWS, Vladimir Zhirinovksiy, the right-wing extremist leader of the Liberal Democratic Party of Russia (LDPR), has apologized for the insults and threats he uttered in Sofia against Germany. "If what I said was taken as insulting, then I am sorry," Zhirinovskiy said in the interview, excerpts of which were prereleased to DPA. He had been "misunderstood." Shortly before Zhirinovkiy made the remarks to which he refers, the German Government had refused him an entry visa. [passage omitted]
